# Git Workflow

## Gitflow Branches

- `main` -- production releases, tagged with semver
- `develop` -- integration branch, PRs merge here
- `feature/YAIT-N-description` -- new features
- `hotfix/YAIT-N-description` -- urgent production fixes
- `release/vX.Y.Z` -- release preparation

Never commit directly to `main` or `develop`.

## Conventional Commits

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`

**Types:** feat, fix, refactor, test, docs, chore, perf

**Scopes:** store, api, handler, mcp, auth, middleware, board, deps, ci

**Examples:**
- `feat(mcp): add delete_project tool`
- `fix(auth): prevent session fixation on login`
- `test(store): add table-driven tests for project CRUD`
- `chore(deps): bump modernc.org/sqlite to v1.49`

**Body:** reference issue with `Refs: YAIT-N`

**Breaking changes:** add `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer

## Rules

- One logical change per commit (atomic commits)
- Rebase feature branches on `develop` before merge
- Squash-merge only if the feature branch has noisy WIP commits
- Delete feature branches after merge
